1. Launch EC2 Instance

Open EC2 → Launch Instance

Name: MyWebAppInstance

AMI: Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS

Instance type: t2.micro

Key pair: Create & download .pem

Security Group:

Allow SSH (22)

Allow HTTP (80)

Allow HTTPS (443)

Launch instance

2. Connect via SSH
chmod 400 MyKeyPair.pem
ssh -i "MyKeyPair.pem" ubuntu@<Public-IP>

3. Update System & Install Packages (APT version)
sudo apt update -y
sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install git
sudo apt install -y docker.io git nano


Start Docker & enable on boot:

sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu


Reconnect SSH to activate group permissions.

4. Create Sample Web App
mkdir mywebapp
cd mywebapp
echo "<h1>Hello from AWS EC2!</h1>" > index.html

Dockerfile
nano Dockerfile


Paste:

FROM alpine:latest
RUN apk --no-cache add nginx
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
EXPOSE 80
CMD ["nginx", "-g", "daemon off;"]

5. Build & Run Docker Container
sudo docker build -t mywebapp-image .
sudo docker run -d -p 80:80 --name mywebapp-container mywebapp-image


Check container:

docker ps

6. Test in Browser

Open:

http://<Public-IP>


You should see “Hello from AWS EC2!”

got to http:ipv4 address
